HEADWORD: Younker
<hw>Youn"ker</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D.
<ets>jonker</ets>, <ets>jonkeer</ets>; <ets>jong</ets> young +
<ets>heer</ets> a lord, sir, gentleman. See <er>Young</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <def>A young person; a stripling; a yonker.</def>
<mark>[Obs. or Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That same <qex>younker</qex> soon was overthrown.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

